title: About me
text: My name is Jena Shah and I am currently a Statistics and Mathematics student at the University of Toronto. I have a passion for numbers, which is why I am dedicated to pursuing a career in actuarial science. My academic background has equipped me with the skills to tackle complex problems and analyze data effectively, while my professional experience has helped me learn how to apply some of those skills to the real-world. I’m particularly interested in exploring how my education can be applied to the stock market. Outside of my studies, I enjoy reading finance books, cooking, and crocheting.

title: About this site
text:
Welcome to my website! I’m using this platform to share my experiences and insights. This website is a space where I currently share a little bit about myself and my experiences (in the CV). But I soon plan on sharing a variety of topics that interest me and the new things I learn in my academic journey as a statistics student.
So whether you’re here to read more into student life, explore different ideas, or simply curious about what I have to share, I hope you find this website engaging and thought-provoking.
Feel free to reach out to me through the e-mail in my CV (shahjenad@gmail.com).
Thank you for visiting!
